---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@components/layout/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Kristian López"
  description="Privacy policy for lopezkristian.com — contact data handling, analytics, retention, and your rights."
  image="/og/og-home.png"
>
  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none prose-headings:text-text-primary prose-p:text-muted prose-li:text-muted prose-a:text-violet-400 prose-strong:text-text-primary">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy describes how lopezkristian.com handles information 
          when you visit it. I take your privacy seriously and aim to be transparent about what 
          data, if any, is collected.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What Data Is Collected</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text-primary">This site does not use accounts, profiling, or tracking cookies by default.</strong>
          Basic server logs (IP address, user-agent, timestamp, requested path) may be processed by the hosting provider
          for operational security, abuse prevention, and reliability.
        </p>
        <p>
          If analytics are enabled via the PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID environment variable, 
          a privacy-first analytics tool may collect aggregate, anonymized pageview data.
          The goal is product improvement, not user profiling.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Contact Form</h2>
        <p>
          If you submit the contact form, the data you provide (name, email, message) is sent
          to an email delivery provider (Resend) and is used solely to respond to your inquiry.
          Form submissions include anti-spam protections (honeypot and client-side rate limiting).
          Messages are retained only as long as needed for communication and follow-up.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Legal Basis</h2>
        <p>
          Personal data sent through the contact form is processed under legitimate interest
          (responding to business and professional inquiries) or your explicit request.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          This site links to external services (GitHub, LinkedIn). Those services have their own 
          privacy policies. I am not responsible for their practices.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are in the EU, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access any data I hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Object to processing</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact me via the contact form.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated occasionally. Significant changes will be noted at the top 
          of this page with the updated date.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
